<refnamediv>
  <refname>stg-sync</refname>
  <refpurpose>Synchronise patches with a branch or a series</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv id="_synopsis">
<blockquote>
<literallayout><emphasis>stg</emphasis> sync [options] [--] [&lt;patch1&gt;] [&lt;patch2&gt;] [&lt;patch3&gt;..&lt;patch4&gt;]</literallayout>
</blockquote>
</refsynopsisdiv>
<refsect1 id="_description">
<title>DESCRIPTION</title>
<simpara>For each of the specified patches perform a three-way merge with the
same patch in the specified branch or series. The command can be used
for keeping patches on several branches in sync. Note that the
operation may fail for some patches because of conflicts. The patches
in the series must apply cleanly.</simpara>
</refsect1>
<refsect1 id="_options">
<title>OPTIONS</title>
<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term>
-a
</term>
<term>
--all
</term>
<listitem>
<simpara>
        Synchronise all the applied patches.
</simpara>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term>
-B REF-BRANCH
</term>
<term>
--ref-branch REF-BRANCH
</term>
<listitem>
<simpara>
        Syncronise patches with BRANCH.
</simpara>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term>
-s SERIES
</term>
<term>
--series SERIES
</term>
<listitem>
<simpara>
        Syncronise patches with SERIES.
</simpara>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>
</refsect1>
